(5.12) .Net Bot

The .Net Bet is a mascot for the entire .Net ecosystem[^6], which includes multiple programming languages such as C#, F#, and VB.Net. The .Net Bot was created by Microsoft as a way to represent the .Net platform and its various components, including the programming languages that run on it. The bot is often depicted as a friendly and approachable character, designed to make the .Net ecosystem more accessible and engaging for developers. While the .Net Bot is not specific to any one programming language, it serves as a unifying mascot for the entire .Net community. 

